race.comment: QUEENSBURY (2) is worth another try. Was a fresh-up winner when well fancied last time but dropped right out. Pulled up lame in hind quarters and has since trialled and is back on track. Well placed here on his best form and gets a chance to atone. THINKING SENSATION (4) is going well and got off the mark with an all the way win last time. Low draw and expected to take catching again. SUNSET BEAUTY (9) has a strong second-up record so don't let her under the guard.  SORRY SAILOR (3) brought up his third career win two back but missed the frame latest when sixth over 1750m at Geelong. Has ability and can bounce back.
